Chris Rowe was plagued by a persistent cough for six months . 
  He visited doctors five times in two months but was told he was most likely suffering a simple virus . 
  In December he was taken to A&E after coughing up blood and complaining of a dull ache in his ribs . 
  X-ray revealed he was suffering an aggressive form of lung cancer that had spread to his liver and bones . 
  The 31-year-old was diagnosed with the cancer in December and told it was inoperable . 
  His wife Kate is expecting their second child in June . 
  Mr Rowe is undergoing chemotherapy to prolong his life . 
 